-th-</i> (not normally reflected in the pronunciation) represents a learned but erroneous attempt to associate it with Greek <i>anthos</i> ‘flower’. In the post-classical period it was a common name, borne by various early saints, most notably a 3rd-century Egyptian hermit monk, who is regarded as the founder of Christian monasticism."],"variants":[{"name":"Antony","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anthony ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anthony Munning was born in 1386, in Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France, his father, Gilbert Munning, was 27 and his mother, Charlotte of Poitiers, was 23. He married Lady Munning about 1407, in Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1443, in Nedging, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 57, and was buried in Nedging, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1386–1443":"1386–1443","1390–1424":"1390–1424","1382–1472":"1382–1472","1408–1462":"1408–1462","1360–1459":"1360–1459","1364–1463":"1364–1463","1385":"1385","1462":"1462","1472":"1472","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","Abt 1407":"umbes 1407","1390":"1390","1459":"1459","from 1434 to 1472":"1434 kuni 1472","1424":"1424","1443":"1443","1386":"1386","1463":"1463","1364":"1364","1408":"1408","Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, Prantsusmaa","of Poictiers, , France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, Prantsusmaa","Nedging, Suffolk, England":"Nedging, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1386–1443":"1386–1443","1390–1424":"1390–1424","1382–1472":"1382–1472","1408–1462":"1408–1462","1360–1459":"1360–1459","1364–1463":"1364–1463","1385":"1385","1462":"1462","1472":"1472","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","Abt 1407":"noin 1407","1390":"1390","1459":"1459","from 1434 to 1472":"vuodesta 1434 vuoteen 1472","1424":"1424","1443":"1443","1386":"1386","1463":"1463","1364":"1364","1408":"1408","Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, Ransk